<span id="freeTextContainer10317167716033994499">I LOVED this book. It&apos;s a story of true friendships which are torn apart by superficial definitions of separateness. It covers the topics of beauty, birth, a parent&apos;s love, a brothers love, unrequited lovers, addiction, the reality of death of old age and the brutality of untimely death. This book tells the story of Ataturk and the Armenian forced migration in a balanced and objective yet intimate way. It tells the story of the unity of the Greeks and the Turks before Wilson&apos;s nationalism had st</span>
  <span id="freeText10317167716033994499" style="display:none">I LOVED this book. It's a story of true friendships which are torn apart by superficial definitions of separateness. It covers the topics of beauty, birth, a parent's love, a brothers love, unrequited lovers, addiction, the reality of death of old age and the brutality of untimely death. This book tells the story of Ataturk and the Armenian forced migration in a balanced and objective yet intimate way. It tells the story of the unity of the Greeks and the Turks before Wilson's nationalism had stained it.</span>
